# Frontend Computation Audit — Move to Backend

## Current Architecture Problem

The frontend fetches **raw entity lists** from three CRUD APIs, then performs all analytics, aggregations, filtering, and scoring **in the browser**:

| API Called | What It Returns |
|---|---|
| `GET /api/Accounts/userid/{userId}` | **All** accounts (full list) |
| `GET /api/Transaction/user/{userId}` | **All** transactions (full list, unbounded) |
| `GET /api/Obligations/dashboard/{userId}` | Dashboard summary + full liability & subscription lists |

> [!CAUTION]
> The Transaction API returns **every transaction ever created** — there's no pagination, no date filtering, no server-side aggregation. As data grows, this will transfer MBs of JSON to the browser on every dashboard load.

