## 💳 Transactions Page — 3 Client-Side Computations

File: [page.tsx](file:///d:/DataSSD/PersonalFinanceApp/personal-finance-app/apps/web/app/my/transactions/page.tsx)

### 11. Summary Cards (Total Bank / Total Credit / Monthly Spending)
- **Lines**: 151-170
- **What it does**: Sums all account balances, all credit card outstanding amounts, and filters this month's expenses from ALL transactions
- **Severity**: 🔴 High — 3 full-list reductions. The monthly spending is particularly expensive.
- **Proposed API**: `GET /api/Transaction/user/{userId}/page-summary`
- **Response**: `{ totalBankBalance, totalCreditOutstanding, thisMonthSpending }`

### 12. Client-Side Filtering & Sorting
- **Lines**: 308-337
- **What it does**: Filters transactions by source type (bank/card), by specific card, and by search query, then sorts by date descending
- **Severity**: 🔴 High — filters/sorts/searches the entire unbounded transaction list in the browser
- **Proposed API**: `GET /api/Transaction/user/{userId}?sourceType=card&cardId=xxx&search=food&page=1&pageSize=15&sortBy=date`
- **Response**: `{ items: [...], totalCount, page, pageSize }`

### 13. Client-Side Pagination
- **Lines**: 816-820, 926-1001
- **What it does**: Slices the (already client-filtered) array. All pages are in memory.
- **Severity**: 🔴 High — pagination should **never** be client-side on an unbounded dataset
- **Proposed API**: Same paginated endpoint as above

